  "elapsed_s": 7.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And the Russians have taken him into a camp-- the Russian concentration camp instead of a German concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And he was in Russia from 1944 until 1951 for six solid years.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "He was a Jew who was trying to escape from the German-- German concentration camp-- got into the Gulag.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it shows-- there's a saying to jump out of the pan into the flame, or something like that.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So he was doing this.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I cannot really complain that I didn't take a chance because the result was very bad.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now, eventually I arrived to Budapest.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I arrived about October 15.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "October 15 was the day when Horthy, the Hungarian ruler at that time, decided that war is going to be over for the Hungarians.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he made an announcement through the radio reporter.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He-- he still didn't speak Hungarian at that time.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So one of my friends with whom I graduated from high school was the one who he and his-- and another radio announcer who was telling the Hungarians that the war is over.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now, the interesting thing that I-- at that time, I arrive-- when I arrived to Budapest, the only solid point was my wife's aunt and uncle.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I visited them over in a Hungarian-- in a Jewish apartment building where the Hungarian [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Arrow Cross Party.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That was the-- this was the fascist party who has checked everybody twice a week-- twice a day-- anytime whenever they did that, so they checked if there was anybody else living in those apartments or only the people who were entitled to stay there.",
      "word_count": 45
    }
  ],
